              <title>Tool: Web Collage</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6016</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6016</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>The <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/yandim/presentation-of-the-web-collage-tool">Web Collage</a> pattern-based tool is presented. This tool allows practitioners to produce IMS-LD compliant learning designs, instantiate them, and eventually deploy them (through Glue!PS) in a Virtual Learning Enviroment (such as Moodle, Wiki or LAMS).</p>
<p>The tool (in its latest version of Web Instance Collage 2) can be <strong>accessed</strong> on-line at <a href="http://pandora.tel.uva.es/wic2/">http://</a><a href="http://pandora.tel.uva.es/wic2/">pandora.tel.uva.es/wic2</a><a href="http://pandora.tel.uva.es/wic2/">/</a>.</p>
<p>A brief <a href="http://youtu.be/0C_AVMQ51Q8">video</a> can be seen at Youtube that describes the complete lifecycle of a learning design using Web Collage (and Glue!PS).</p>
<p>A <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/yandim/implementing-the-pyramidbased-educational-scenario-using-wb-collage-worksheet">Worksheet</a> is provided to guide the <strong>production of the learning design</strong> corresponding to the sample pyramid-based educational scenario.</p>
<p>Another <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/yandim/worksheet-of-deploying-a-learning-design-produced-by-web-collage-in-moodle">Worksheet</a> presents the way the derived learning design of the sample educational scenario is <strong>deployed</strong> (through Glue!PS) in the Moodle Virtual Learning.Environment.</p>
<p>Finally you can engage in an intoductory activity here: <a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloudscape/view/2852">http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloudscape/view/2852</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
