                    <item>
              <title>Using the e-Design Template for the nQuire learning design</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5863</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5863</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>To start the challenge, I summarised the learning design for the Microclimate topic as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 1: Students read summary material in 'Find my Topic' section. Students write own overview of what they will be focussing on.</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 2: Students write hypothesis in 'Hypothesis' section</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 3: Students read information on data and write own plan for data collection</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 4: Students collect data using method chosen and enter in 'Collect Evidence' section</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 5: Students view data using graphs etc in 'Analyse' section</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 6: Students write conclusions in 'Respond' section</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 7: Students share conclusions with others and discuss. Write summary in 'Share and Discuss' section</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Activity 8: Students write comments on investigation in 'Reflect' section</li>
</ul>
<div>There were insufficient details in the nQuire learning design to comment on the timings of the activities, the types of interactions and the assessment. However, it was possible to identify different levels of scaffolding of the activities and they have mapped easily to the template.&nbsp;</div>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Tue, 18 Oct 2011 11:48:34 +0000</pubDate>
            </item>
                    <item>
              <title>WebInstanceCollage, a pattern-based LD tool allowing particularization of groups and participants</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5861</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5861</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><a title="WebInstanceCollage LD tool" href="http://pandora.tel.uva.es/wic/" target="_blank">WebInstanceCollage</a>&nbsp;is a web-based learning design authoring tool, which builds upon the idea of <a title="CLFPs @ EduTech wiki" href="http://edutechwiki.unige.ch/en/Collaborative_learning_flow_pattern" target="_blank">collaborative learning flow patterns</a>&nbsp;(e.g. Jigsaw, Pyramid...) and assessment patterns, enabling and guiding teachers in building complex collaborative activities using graphical metaphors for these patterns, and combining and nesting them in various ways. &nbsp;The resulting designs can be exported using IMS-LD (level A).</p>
<p>The tool also allows for the particularization (or instantiation) of the designs to different particular situations, allowing for the definition of the number of groups and the participants in each of these groups (which can be extracted from existing LMSs).</p>
<p>When using this tool together with the <a title="Official GLUE! website" href="http://www.gsic.uva.es/glue/" target="_blank">GLUE! architecture</a> for integration of LMSs and external Web 2.0 tools (e.g. GoogleDocs, MediaWiki), a teacher can now design this kind of complex activities and deploy them in multiple LMSs like Moodle (see&nbsp;<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pCLw9sf68kA">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pCLw9sf68kA</a>).</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Installation instructions:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p><a title="WebInstanceCollage LD tool" href="http://pandora.tel.uva.es/wic/" target="_blank">WebInstanceCollage</a> is a web-based tool, so no installation is required (only a very simple registration is needed to use the tool).</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Tue, 18 Oct 2011 10:11:31 +0000</pubDate>
