              <title>Locating learning design research</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/608</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/608</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><img align="absmiddle" alt="" src="http://www.e4innovation.com/images/goodyear.jpg" /></p>
<p><strong>Figure 1 - locating learning design research in Pasteur's quadrant<br />
</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>Pasteurs&rsquo; quadrant to often used to describe and understand the nature and</p>
<p>purpose of research</p>
<p></p>
<p>A 2D-framework can be used with Research as 'use inspired' y/n cf</p>
<p>'fundamental understanding' y/n</p>
<p>Within this framework Pasteur&rsquo;s quadrant on the bottom right of the diagram is</p>
<p>about both use inspired but also towards fundamental understanding</p>
<p>Learning design sits within the same quadrant<br />
<br />
1. In terms of fundamental understanding the focus of learning design research is: <br />
Teachers&rsquo; design practices<br />
Design qualities<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Valid <br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Well-specified <br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interpreter<br />
<br />
2. In terms of use inspiration, the focus of learning design research is:</p>
<p>Improvement of education through improvement of &lsquo;teaching as design&rsquo;</p>
<p>through provision of better tools and methods</p>]]></description>
